text = "Pick and place
[ul]
Choose a piece from your hand.
Click the piece you want to play.
Select a row or column on the board.
Click the arrow pointing the direction you want to push - the arrow shows which way the line will slide.
[/ul]
[br]
Valid moves
[ul]
The game blocks invalid moves automatically.
You may play if your piece matches the color on the opposite end of the chosen row or column.
You may play if your piece does not match any color in that row or column.
You may NOT play if your piece matches a color inside the row/column but not the opposite end.
[/ul]
[br]
Sliding and hand refill
[ul]
Sliding effect: the selected row or column shifts by one space in the arrowâ€™s direction.
The piece at the far end is pushed out and returned to the draw pile.
After the move, your hand refills back to 3 pieces.
[/ul]
[br]
Pink ability pieces
[ul]
When played, a Pink piece lets you swap any two pieces on the board (Mushrooms cannot be swapped).
Pink pieces are not placed on the board; after use they return to the draw pile.
[/ul]
[br]
Mushroom reset and scoring
[ul]
If all Mushrooms are removed from the board, the center tile is replaced with a new Mushroom.
First player to reach 7 points wins
[/ul]"
